1
00:00:41,124 --> 00:00:42,417
Burger Mcjo?

2
00:00:42,500 --> 00:00:43,752
Burger McQueen?

3
00:00:43,835 --> 00:00:45,503
<i>And he has a background</i>
<i>in forensic accounting.</i>

4
00:00:45,587 --> 00:00:47,255
<i>He is assigned to track down the money.</i>

5
00:00:47,338 --> 00:00:51,009
So we can use his expertise
to map out their financial network.

6
00:00:55,430 --> 00:00:56,514
You did nothing.

7
00:00:56,598 --> 00:00:59,142
<i>You let Isabella decide for our daughter?</i>

8
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:04,355
Whatever she wants, let's give it to her.

9
00:01:06,316 --> 00:01:09,652
Agent Alex, these are all the files
you asked for from me.

10
00:01:09,736 --> 00:01:12,280
You're already working?
You're such a workaholic.

11
00:01:16,451 --> 00:01:19,204
So I hope both of you will behave
while I'm working.

12
00:01:31,883 --> 00:01:33,968
I can't do this anymore. I hate this.

13
00:01:34,052 --> 00:01:37,430
Now Agent Alex is our babysitter, too.

14
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:40,892
Sorry, sweetheart. This is my fault.

15
00:01:40,975 --> 00:01:43,436
If only I hadn't come up with
our ice cream date.

16
00:01:43,520 --> 00:01:45,730
Then we wouldn't have
another person watching us.

17
00:01:48,858 --> 00:01:51,694
I know you only did that to make me happy

18
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:53,154
and you did make me happy,

19
00:01:53,238 --> 00:01:55,073
so thank you very, very much.

20
00:01:56,157 --> 00:01:58,159
I'm just annoyed because

21
00:01:58,243 --> 00:02:00,411
I can't control the situation.

22
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:10,255
There you go, sweetheart.
Just keep walking.

23
00:02:10,338 --> 00:02:14,092
As they say, walking helps lower
your cortisol levels.

24
00:02:14,175 --> 00:02:15,885
Which are your stress hormones.

25
00:02:16,928 --> 00:02:17,804
So that's good.

26
00:02:17,887 --> 00:02:19,055
I have an idea!

27
00:02:19,639 --> 00:02:20,473
What?

28
00:02:21,307 --> 00:02:25,103
If Agent Alex wants to stay here with us,

29
00:02:26,604 --> 00:02:29,190
then she should be willing to put up with

30
00:02:29,274 --> 00:02:31,484
whatever she ends up hearing.

31
00:02:53,131 --> 00:02:54,215
<i>Blah-blah-blah.</i>

32
00:02:54,883 --> 00:02:56,050
<i>Just kidding!</i>

33
00:02:57,510 --> 00:02:58,511
<i>Sweetheart!</i>

34
00:02:58,595 --> 00:02:59,637
<i>Yes?</i>

35
00:02:59,721 --> 00:03:01,389
<i>You're so funny!</i>

36
00:03:01,472 --> 00:03:04,100
<i>Of course, I know! I really am!</i>

37
00:03:04,183 --> 00:03:05,602
<i>You're really something, sweetheart!</i>

38
00:03:06,102 --> 00:03:07,103
<i>You know me!</i>

39
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:08,813
<i>Sweetheart!</i>

40
00:03:08,897 --> 00:03:10,189
Oh, boy!

41
00:03:10,273 --> 00:03:12,692
The spicy part has started.

42
00:03:17,739 --> 00:03:19,616
It's like an island tropic,

43
00:03:19,699 --> 00:03:21,034
and the best part
is there's a third wheel,

44
00:03:21,117 --> 00:03:22,493
who isn't really a third wheel.

45
00:03:22,577 --> 00:03:24,329
Because she can't say
that she's loving him too much.

46
00:03:24,412 --> 00:03:26,164
Heart-stopping.

47
00:03:26,873 --> 00:03:27,665
Break it down.

48
00:03:28,499 --> 00:03:30,209
What, are you rapping over there?

49
00:03:31,377 --> 00:03:33,296
You know you're here to work.

50
00:03:33,379 --> 00:03:35,506
Not to gossip about everyone.

51
00:03:36,466 --> 00:03:38,843
I'm just telling the truth, and besides,

52
00:03:39,385 --> 00:03:41,012
you're the real gossipers here.

53
00:03:41,095 --> 00:03:43,306
You installed CCTV cameras in their room.

54
00:03:45,058 --> 00:03:47,101
It's for safety reasons.

55
00:03:48,311 --> 00:03:50,104
All I'm saying is,

56
00:03:50,188 --> 00:03:52,607
if you really want to know

57
00:03:52,690 --> 00:03:54,651
what they're doing,

58
00:03:54,734 --> 00:03:57,237
then go to the security room.

59
00:03:59,614 --> 00:04:01,991
<i>Two lovers trapped inside the room.</i>

60
00:04:02,075 --> 00:04:03,368
<i>That third wheel is intense.</i>

61
00:04:03,451 --> 00:04:04,953
<i>Jealous but can't admit it.</i>

62
00:04:05,036 --> 00:04:06,788
<i>She's so mad at me, it's crazy!</i>

63
00:04:06,871 --> 00:04:09,624
<i>I have no idea what she's going to do.</i>

64
00:04:09,707 --> 00:04:12,627
<i>She's thinking hard, she doesn't know</i>

65
00:04:12,710 --> 00:04:15,630
<i>what she's going to do.</i>
<i>She's coming down, here she comes!</i>

66
00:04:15,713 --> 00:04:17,257
<i>Things are about to get chaotic!</i>

67
00:04:21,886 --> 00:04:24,472
We really are perfect for each other.

68
00:04:35,149 --> 00:04:36,025
Hey!

69
00:04:36,609 --> 00:04:38,695
-Bro, how are you?
-Hi!

70
00:04:38,778 --> 00:04:39,779
I missed you so much.

71
00:04:39,862 --> 00:04:41,698
-I missed you so much!
-Gosh…

72
00:04:43,324 --> 00:04:44,325
Come here.

73
00:04:46,202 --> 00:04:48,621
Wait, why are you guys here?

74
00:04:48,705 --> 00:04:50,707
Isn't it obvious? We're on vacation!

75
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:54,752
But how did you know where we were?

76
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:56,296
It's not hard to find.

77
00:04:56,379 --> 00:04:58,631
Actually, everything was posted
on Sofie's Fishbook.

78
00:04:58,715 --> 00:05:00,091
Seriously, with complete details!

79
00:05:01,009 --> 00:05:02,343
Complete details?

80
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:05,513
So you saw our exact location
just from that?

81
00:05:05,596 --> 00:05:07,348
Because of Sofie's post?

82
00:05:07,432 --> 00:05:12,395
Oh, Angelito.
That's the power of social media.

83
00:05:12,478 --> 00:05:13,646
Yes.

84
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:15,023
And you, Sofie,

85
00:05:15,106 --> 00:05:18,192
your profile is really easy to stalk.

86
00:05:18,276 --> 00:05:20,445
If I were you, I wouldn't post
too many details

87
00:05:20,528 --> 00:05:22,947
or your real-time location.

88
00:05:23,031 --> 00:05:25,658
Everything I post is safe, and besides,

89
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:27,118
it's all on CF.

90
00:05:28,328 --> 00:05:29,579
What's CF?

91
00:05:30,455 --> 00:05:32,457
Close Friends.

92
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:34,834
Just kidding!

93
00:05:35,418 --> 00:05:38,254
It just means only friends can see it.

94
00:05:38,838 --> 00:05:40,757
That's what Close Friends means.

95
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,093
I'm not really on Fishbook.

96
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:46,596
-I'm more of a TokTok guy.
-Obviously.

97
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:47,805
You know what,

98
00:05:47,889 --> 00:05:49,807
I'll invite you to my house. Let's go.

99
00:05:49,891 --> 00:05:51,350
I'll introduce you to my parents.

100
00:05:51,434 --> 00:05:53,853
-Hey, let's go!
-I'm so excited!

101
00:05:53,936 --> 00:05:55,146
Okay!

102
00:05:55,229 --> 00:05:56,397
How do I click this?

103
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:58,066
-Just hold it.
-Hold it?

104
00:05:58,149 --> 00:05:59,692
-I hold the clicker?
-Yes.

105
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:01,152
Like this?

106
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:13,331
Alex, you're not doing this to gossip.

107
00:06:13,831 --> 00:06:16,084
You're doing this because
you just want to know

108
00:06:16,167 --> 00:06:18,336
what they're doing
without alarming anyone.

109
00:06:24,342 --> 00:06:25,718
Who am I kidding?

110
00:06:59,544 --> 00:07:00,878
Why is there no feed?

111
00:07:03,631 --> 00:07:05,675
Here, it's not working.

112
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:14,976
Do you know why there's no feed in Room 1?

113
00:07:15,059 --> 00:07:16,269
Did the camera break?

114
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:18,771
They probably covered it again.

115
00:07:18,855 --> 00:07:20,898
I just checked that earlier.

116
00:07:21,524 --> 00:07:22,942
Those two are really something, huh?

117
00:07:23,609 --> 00:07:24,944
Look away for just a second,

118
00:07:25,027 --> 00:07:26,571
and you'll get played.

119
00:07:48,092 --> 00:07:50,011
-Look at that Isabela.
-Please show it to my followers.

120
00:07:50,761 --> 00:07:53,139
Like an Italian,

121
00:07:53,222 --> 00:07:54,182
food vlogger.

122
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:55,224
Doing mukbang.

123
00:07:55,308 --> 00:07:56,517
Jeez.

124
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:57,435
Oh, my gosh.

125
00:07:57,518 --> 00:08:00,646
Who would think
that's a big-time mafia boss.

126
00:08:00,730 --> 00:08:03,816
If she lived a normal life,
maybe she'd be in the food industry.

127
00:08:07,987 --> 00:08:09,238
Fair enough.

128
00:08:10,239 --> 00:08:11,824
If she's going to stay here,

129
00:08:11,908 --> 00:08:13,075
Viktor,

130
00:08:13,576 --> 00:08:15,578
maybe we can charge her rent?

131
00:08:16,370 --> 00:08:17,580
Exactly.

132
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:21,250
-Things are expensive these days.
-True!

133
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:23,586
And she eats a lot.

134
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:26,881
We can use her rent fee
to pay for her food.

135
00:08:26,964 --> 00:08:28,382
Maybe around,

136
00:08:55,868 --> 00:08:58,538
-70K for monthly rent.
-Right.

137
00:08:58,621 --> 00:08:59,664
-Period.
-Okay.

138
00:08:59,747 --> 00:09:01,290
Would you like to try our banana fritters?

139
00:09:01,374 --> 00:09:02,625
-Oh, please, thank you.
-She's always hungry.

140
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:03,834
Sorry.

141
00:09:06,504 --> 00:09:07,922
It's okay, I'll handle it.

142
00:09:18,349 --> 00:09:19,934
You're pretending again,

143
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:23,437
but you're also interested
in what the two of them are doing.

144
00:09:23,521 --> 00:09:26,232
Welcome to Big Sister's house!

145
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:29,402
Again, I'm just doing my job.

146
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,446
Try lying to someone else.

147
00:09:33,030 --> 00:09:33,948
You know,

148
00:09:34,031 --> 00:09:37,076
it's natural for the two of them
to be doing that.

149
00:09:37,159 --> 00:09:38,786
That they're "doing stuff."

150
00:09:40,204 --> 00:09:41,163
Doing stuff?

151
00:09:43,332 --> 00:09:44,458
Playing Jenga.

152
00:09:47,545 --> 00:09:48,963
If they're both bored,

153
00:09:49,046 --> 00:09:52,049
I also have a way to make
things interesting in this house.

154
00:09:52,133 --> 00:09:53,301
Okay?

155
00:10:06,981 --> 00:10:09,400
<i>Mikoy, seriously!</i>

156
00:10:09,483 --> 00:10:12,653
<i>Not there!</i>

157
00:10:12,737 --> 00:10:17,950
<i>-I'm here!</i>
<i>-Stop! Sweetheart, not there!</i>

158
00:10:22,830 --> 00:10:24,874
<i>-Sweetheart!</i>
<i>-Yes?</i>

159
00:10:24,957 --> 00:10:27,043
<i>You're so funny!</i>

160
00:10:27,126 --> 00:10:29,545
<i>Of course, I know! I really am!</i>

161
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:31,714
<i>You're really something, sweetheart!</i>

162
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:42,183
<i>Mikoy, I told you to stop!</i>

163
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:50,441
<i>We're just playing.</i>

164
00:10:54,487 --> 00:10:58,574
<i>-Ouch! That hurts!</i>
<i>-Oh, does it hurt?</i>

165
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:01,410
<i>Sweetheart!</i>

166
00:11:01,494 --> 00:11:03,371
<i>Sweetheart, really!</i>

167
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:14,382
Wow, I'm exhausted!

168
00:11:16,092 --> 00:11:17,093
Me too.

169
00:11:18,135 --> 00:11:21,389
You know, pillow fights
are actually fun, huh?

170
00:11:23,182 --> 00:11:25,768
Don't you have slumber parties
for pillow fights?

171
00:11:27,103 --> 00:11:28,354
No.

172
00:11:28,437 --> 00:11:30,189
There's no such thing for the poor.

173
00:11:31,607 --> 00:11:34,527
Slumber means overnight, right?

174
00:11:35,152 --> 00:11:36,195
We don't have that.

175
00:11:36,278 --> 00:11:38,697
We don't do overnight, only overtime.

176
00:11:38,781 --> 00:11:40,825
Overtime work,

177
00:11:40,908 --> 00:11:42,910
so there's food for the next day.

178
00:11:43,494 --> 00:11:44,912
And the pillow fight?

179
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:50,000
Oh, please. Try getting hit
by our hard pillows.

180
00:11:50,084 --> 00:11:52,294
Let's see if you can still get up.

181
00:11:54,004 --> 00:11:55,214
So dramatic!

182
00:11:56,006 --> 00:11:57,133
It's true!

183
00:11:58,259 --> 00:12:01,303
The pillows you see in that house?
The soft ones?

184
00:12:01,387 --> 00:12:02,221
Oh, please.

185
00:12:02,304 --> 00:12:05,099
Those are from everything
I worked for in Prague.

186
00:12:05,766 --> 00:12:08,519
So you know, I'm really lucky I met you.

187
00:12:09,311 --> 00:12:10,479
Because

188
00:12:11,147 --> 00:12:13,816
you really changed my life, somehow.

189
00:12:18,779 --> 00:12:21,407
I should be the one saying that.

190
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:32,293
Who would've thought that one day,

191
00:12:32,376 --> 00:12:35,421
I'd be fighting for my freedom.

192
00:12:37,339 --> 00:12:40,426
I could only dream about it before,
but now it feels like,

193
00:12:41,969 --> 00:12:43,804
it's within reach.

194
00:12:47,850 --> 00:12:49,101
You know what?

195
00:13:01,780 --> 00:13:03,240
Why are you so sweet?

196
00:13:04,283 --> 00:13:05,451
Did you do something?

197
00:13:06,452 --> 00:13:07,578
No!

198
00:13:07,661 --> 00:13:11,373
Come on, I just said "I love you"
and suddenly I'm guilty?

199
00:13:11,457 --> 00:13:15,628
Because usually I'm the one
who says "I love you" first.

200
00:13:16,170 --> 00:13:18,214
I go first.

201
00:13:23,177 --> 00:13:24,887
I don't know about you.

202
00:13:25,596 --> 00:13:28,682
All right, I'm going
to take a shower, I feel sticky.

203
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:30,643
Wait, are you sure?

204
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:32,228
Don't you want round 2?

205
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:36,690
All right then, fine, never mind.

206
00:13:36,774 --> 00:13:39,902
Go take a shower, I'll drink some water.

207
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:41,070
Okay?

208
00:14:37,877 --> 00:14:39,086
What happened?

209
00:14:39,753 --> 00:14:41,881
I was just changing the light bulb.

210
00:14:42,548 --> 00:14:43,716
I'll help you.

211
00:14:43,799 --> 00:14:45,092
No, no, it's fine.

212
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:46,760
Can you turn it on?

213
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:48,637
Okay.

214
00:14:51,515 --> 00:14:52,433
There!

215
00:14:52,516 --> 00:14:53,559
Hey, hey!

216
00:15:15,831 --> 00:15:17,291
What is happening?

217
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:30,179
This is because Alex was changing
a light bulb and lost her balance.

218
00:15:30,679 --> 00:15:32,681
Good thing I was here to catch her.

219
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,729
You know?
I feel like I've seen that before.

220
00:15:41,649 --> 00:15:43,025
What are you doing here, sweetheart?

221
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:53,285
Well I think I also need a drink.

222
00:15:54,161 --> 00:15:55,412
You want juice?

223
00:15:56,956 --> 00:15:57,790
Sure.

224
00:15:58,499 --> 00:15:59,500
Okay.

225
00:16:05,047 --> 00:16:08,592
Alex, are you okay?

226
00:16:09,635 --> 00:16:10,469
Of course.

227
00:16:42,543 --> 00:16:43,419
Tess!

228
00:16:44,461 --> 00:16:45,462
-Tess.
-Yes!

229
00:16:45,546 --> 00:16:47,089
Yes, Captain Pepe?

230
00:16:47,172 --> 00:16:50,175
Looks like someone wants to apply
as a baker again.

231
00:16:50,259 --> 00:16:51,927
Again? Who is it this time?

232
00:16:53,053 --> 00:16:54,346
What happened to the motorcycle?

233
00:16:54,430 --> 00:16:56,557
The battery keeps dying.

234
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:58,684
I just fixed that yesterday.

235
00:16:58,767 --> 00:17:01,395
Oh, no, it's Angelito again.

236
00:17:01,478 --> 00:17:03,814
You know, it's Angelito's friends,

237
00:17:03,897 --> 00:17:05,232
they're considered friends
of the Pinagpala.

238
00:17:05,315 --> 00:17:06,984
So it's fine, we're good here.

239
00:17:07,067 --> 00:17:07,985
Okay, thank you.

240
00:17:08,068 --> 00:17:09,611
-Let's go inside.
-Okay.

241
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:12,573
So, what? Introduce them, come on.

242
00:17:13,323 --> 00:17:14,450
Mom. Dad.

243
00:17:14,533 --> 00:17:16,243
By the way, this is Laurence
and this is Luisa Mae.

244
00:17:16,326 --> 00:17:17,036
-Hello.
-Hello.

245
00:17:17,119 --> 00:17:19,788
Laurence is my roommate in the dorm.

246
00:17:20,456 --> 00:17:22,041
And this is Luisa Mae--

247
00:17:22,124 --> 00:17:23,751
Wait, let me guess.

248
00:17:23,834 --> 00:17:27,546
Luisa Mae is Laurence's girlfriend?

249
00:17:27,629 --> 00:17:28,756
You're a couple!

250
00:17:29,673 --> 00:17:34,053
No, we actually have more
of a connection with Angelito.

251
00:17:40,893 --> 00:17:42,561
Do you want to go see our oven?

252
00:17:42,644 --> 00:17:44,646
Let me show you how we make
the special torta.

253
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:45,689
Let's go.

254
00:17:45,773 --> 00:17:48,275
Mom, dad, we'll just go inside. Let's go.

255
00:17:48,358 --> 00:17:49,443
I'll give you a tour here. Come on.

256
00:17:49,526 --> 00:17:50,736
-Excuse us.
-We're going.

257
00:17:50,819 --> 00:17:52,237
-We'll stay there.
-Okay, then.

258
00:17:52,321 --> 00:17:53,655
Come on, let's go!

259
00:17:53,739 --> 00:17:54,782
Here.

260
00:17:54,865 --> 00:17:56,283
Honey, you know,

261
00:17:56,909 --> 00:17:59,078
that might actually
be the trend right now,

262
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:02,748
dating someone else's partner as your own,

263
00:18:02,831 --> 00:18:04,416
and then, well, it's legal.

264
00:18:04,500 --> 00:18:07,711
I think that's called
an open relationship.

265
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:12,216
Kids these days, really.

266
00:18:12,299 --> 00:18:13,258
Right?

267
00:18:13,342 --> 00:18:16,970
I guess back in our day, that existed too.

268
00:18:17,054 --> 00:18:19,181
We just didn't have a term for it,

269
00:18:19,264 --> 00:18:21,517
for the label, right?

270
00:18:22,726 --> 00:18:25,813
I think
I may have underestimated Angelito.

271
00:18:26,396 --> 00:18:27,940
Angelito? Why?

272
00:18:28,774 --> 00:18:30,484
He's still into it.

273
00:18:31,944 --> 00:18:34,363
Look at you being a father.

274
00:18:35,864 --> 00:18:37,407
Is the oven getting hot?

275
00:18:37,991 --> 00:18:39,034
It's rising.

276
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,037
Oh, what a hot oven!

277
00:18:43,205 --> 00:18:45,040
Do you see those?

278
00:18:45,666 --> 00:18:48,377
Those are the tortas Sofie baked.

279
00:18:48,460 --> 00:18:49,503
Cool, right?

280
00:18:50,671 --> 00:18:52,756
It's just that the shape isn't perfect

281
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:54,133
but it's delicious.

282
00:18:54,883 --> 00:18:57,469
Wow, teach me how to bake too.

283
00:18:57,553 --> 00:18:59,096
I want to bake something for you.

284
00:19:00,556 --> 00:19:02,432
Okay sure, when do you want to?

285
00:19:03,308 --> 00:19:04,309
Tomorrow?

286
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:08,522
Wow, with Luisa you say yes right away,
but with me it's a lecture first.

287
00:19:11,108 --> 00:19:12,901
Isn't he sweet?

288
00:19:12,985 --> 00:19:15,028
He's always like that when it comes to me.

289
00:19:15,112 --> 00:19:16,530
Like he can't say no.

290
00:19:17,614 --> 00:19:18,657
Don't worry.

291
00:19:19,575 --> 00:19:20,826
I'll be the one saying yes to you.

292
00:19:21,660 --> 00:19:22,661
Whatever you order.

293
00:19:23,579 --> 00:19:25,789
As long as it's not math.

294
00:19:25,873 --> 00:19:27,875
That's Angelito's specialty.

295
00:19:30,252 --> 00:19:31,336
Really?

296
00:19:32,171 --> 00:19:33,505
You'll say yes to anything?

297
00:19:34,298 --> 00:19:35,299
Of course.

298
00:19:35,799 --> 00:19:37,634
You already made me say yes, didn't you?

299
00:19:38,343 --> 00:19:39,845
But it would be better if,

300
00:19:40,929 --> 00:19:42,514
I could also make you say yes.

301
00:19:46,351 --> 00:19:47,394
Wait, wait.

302
00:19:48,145 --> 00:19:50,647
You're kinda vague.

303
00:20:05,996 --> 00:20:07,206
<i>Chow!</i>

304
00:20:08,665 --> 00:20:09,750
<i>Tongits!</i>

305
00:20:10,292 --> 00:20:12,044
I win again!

306
00:20:12,127 --> 00:20:14,922
If this were a reality show
and this was the task…

307
00:20:15,005 --> 00:20:16,757
I'd always be the winner.

308
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:19,218
Again?

309
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:22,262
Wait, wait, are you cheating?

310
00:20:22,346 --> 00:20:23,430
You've been at it!

311
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:25,349
You always win!

312
00:20:30,312 --> 00:20:31,688
I knew it!

313
00:20:35,943 --> 00:20:38,237
It's boring if he's
always the one winning.

314
00:20:38,320 --> 00:20:39,446
Exactly!

315
00:20:39,529 --> 00:20:40,447
Right?

316
00:21:02,678 --> 00:21:04,429
There's a lot of waiting here.

317
00:21:04,513 --> 00:21:06,181
And even more hiding.

318
00:21:09,768 --> 00:21:12,437
La Morte Bianca already has the bomb.

319
00:21:12,521 --> 00:21:17,150
Meanwhile, we're just here fixing
a busted lightbulb, right?

320
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:23,031
We need to wait for all
law enforcement agencies to align

321
00:21:23,115 --> 00:21:24,908
before we make a move.

322
00:21:24,992 --> 00:21:26,493
Because if we act now,

323
00:21:26,576 --> 00:21:29,371
there's a chance of a misencounter
with other police units,

324
00:21:29,454 --> 00:21:30,789
or even the military.

325
00:21:33,417 --> 00:21:36,336
And since the threat is national in scope,

326
00:21:36,420 --> 00:21:39,131
we need to update everyone at the top.

327
00:21:40,674 --> 00:21:44,052
And that's why the government
will always be a step behind

328
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,554
when it comes to criminals.

329
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:47,347
Okay. Op! Op! Op!

330
00:21:47,431 --> 00:21:49,182
Let's pause the discussion for now, okay?

331
00:21:49,266 --> 00:21:51,768
I'm going to get some drinks!

332
00:21:51,852 --> 00:21:52,769
I'll come with you.

333
00:21:52,853 --> 00:21:54,187
Okay, let's go!

334
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:16,293
Open up where?

335
00:22:18,503 --> 00:22:19,796
Come on!

336
00:22:20,297 --> 00:22:22,799
It's only now that
I'm really getting to know you.

337
00:22:25,719 --> 00:22:27,471
You know, for an agent,

338
00:22:27,554 --> 00:22:29,765
you're not that good at hiding, huh?

339
00:22:42,569 --> 00:22:47,157
The first time I met you, you were
just pretending to be Mikoy's friend.

340
00:22:51,078 --> 00:22:52,662
Mikoy!

341
00:22:59,419 --> 00:23:00,629
So.

342
00:23:00,712 --> 00:23:02,172
Did you mean it?

343
00:23:05,383 --> 00:23:06,760
When you said,

344
00:23:07,511 --> 00:23:09,721
that Mikoy loves me very much.

345
00:23:10,514 --> 00:23:12,557
That I don't need to worry.

346
00:23:12,641 --> 00:23:15,811
That I should feel secure
in his love for me.

347
00:23:18,688 --> 00:23:20,273
You have nothing to worry about.

348
00:23:20,857 --> 00:23:22,317
Mikoy loves you very much.

349
00:23:26,154 --> 00:23:27,489
Or…

350
00:23:27,572 --> 00:23:30,367
was that just one of your lies?

351
00:23:32,744 --> 00:23:35,622
Because, between two women, Alex,

352
00:24:10,532 --> 00:24:11,825
What do you want to wish?

353
00:24:12,659 --> 00:24:14,327
I wish

354
00:24:16,204 --> 00:24:19,958
that we can be free.

355
00:24:20,041 --> 00:24:24,045
No agency. No Concordat.

356
00:24:24,129 --> 00:24:25,589
Just the two of us.

357
00:24:25,672 --> 00:24:27,549
<i>In our own world.</i>

358
00:24:35,348 --> 00:24:38,059
Did you find them both?

359
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:38,894
Not yet.

360
00:24:38,977 --> 00:24:43,106
But we sent some people to check the place
where we think they're hiding.

361
00:24:43,190 --> 00:24:47,652
Report to me once you find them.

362
00:24:55,035 --> 00:24:59,873
It doesn't matter who or how many
have admired him.

363
00:24:59,956 --> 00:25:04,502
<i>The important thing is, he chose me.</i>
<i>And he loves me.</i>

364
00:25:05,337 --> 00:25:09,341
Then in that case,
you have nothing to worry about.

